      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Acetaminophen is usually the go-to choice when you're on warfarin, so you're on the right track. For a standard dose, taking it as directed on the bottle is generally safe. Just make sure you don't exceed the maximum daily limit, as that can be tough on your liver. If you're still worried, try to get a quick consult with a nurse line, but for now, acetaminophen is your best bet.",
      "source": "target",
